  "text": "That activation of infectivity depends on proteolytic modification of the haemagglutinin and not on other viral surface components was demonstrated by experiments employing recom binants that contained the HA of virus N and the neuraminidase of fowl plague virus or vice versa (table 2) . Only recombinant viruses possessing virus N haemagglutinin exhibited hostspecific variation of the HA cleavability, activation by trypsin and infectivity, features typical for virus N. These features are not found with the recombinants possessing the neura minidase of virus N and the haemagglutinin of FPV [CITATION_1] .",
